import React from 'react'
import { View, Text,Image,Dimensions } from 'react-native'
import {MaterialIcons} from '@expo/vector-icons'
export default function Card() {
    return (
        <View  style={{elevation:3,marginBottom:20}}>
            <Image 
            source={{uri:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTMqSZ5J8sMojfz--IFIHPcGlClswfexRSRcg&usqp=CAU"}}
            style={{
                width:"100%",
                height:220
                
            }}
            />
        <View style={{display:"flex",flexDirection:"row",margin:10}}>
            <View>
                <MaterialIcons name="account-circle" size={45} color="gray"/>
            </View>
            <View style={{marginLeft:10,display:"flex",flexDirection:"column"}}>
                <Text  style={{fontSize:16,color:"white",width:Dimensions.get('screen').width-80}} ellipsizeMode="tail" numberOfLines={1}>
                    Definition and Usage. The background-image property sets one or more background images for an element
                </Text>
                <Text style={{fontSize:12,width:'80%',color:"white"}}>Define The background property.</Text>
            </View>
        </View>



        </View>
    )
}
